# Modern UI Standard (Finely Cred)

## Layout
- Prefer **page-level scrolling**. Avoid tall nested scroll containers (`overflow-y-auto` + fixed heights) unless absolutely necessary.
- Use **wider content** on admin/portal pages: default to `max-w-7xl` (or larger) for data-heavy screens.
- Keep long content **collapsed by default** using accordions/`<details>`; show previews + “Expand” instead of giant always-open boxes.

## Cards (no “big grey boxes”)
- Use **card grids** for lists (`grid gap-4`) instead of stacked full-width blocks.
- Promote key info into **KPI cards** (counts, totals, missing items, status) at the top of a page/section.
- Keep cards visually premium: subtle borders, glass surfaces, strong typography hierarchy.

## Interactions
- For long bodies (letters, logs, guides), provide:
  - **Compact header card** (title, meta, actions)
  - **Expand** for full body (page scroll), not internal scrolling panes.

## Selection-heavy workflows (premium pattern)
- For workflows with many selectable items (disputes, documents, tasks):
  - Show a **KPI row first**: selected count, missing requirements, readiness %, last action.
  - Use **grouped collapsible cards** (`<details>`) to avoid long walls of UI.
  - Use a **focused detail panel** (right column on desktop) for editing one item at a time.
  - Provide a **sticky action bar** at the top or bottom of the page (not inline buttons on every row).
- Never “fix” ugly layouts by adding more nested scrolling. Prefer collapsing, grouping, and focused panels.

## Confirmations + permissions (safety UX)
- For destructive actions (delete letters, revoke access):
  - Use **2-step confirmation** (modal + explicit typed phrase like `DELETE`).
  - Prefer **Archive** over Delete for partner-facing flows (undoable).
  - Gate destructive actions behind **permissions** (admin-only hard delete).

## Code pattern
Example (KPI row + collapsible cards):

```tsx
<div className="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
  <KpiCard label="Letters" value={letters.length} hint="Generated" tone="amber" />
  <KpiCard label="Missing evidence" value={missingEv} tone="violet" />
</div>

<div className="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  {items.map((x) => (
    <details key={x.id} className="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-5">
      <summary className="cursor-pointer select-none text-white font-semibold">
        {x.title}
      </summary>
      <div className="mt-4 text-white/70">{x.body}</div>
    </details>
  ))}
</div>
```

